Sentencas: A series of Nd0.8-xSr0.2CaxCoO3-delta(x = 0, 0.05, 0.1, 0.15, 0.2) cathode materials was synthesized by sol-gel method.
Titulo: Evaluation of Nd0.8-xSr0.2CaxCoO3-δ(x=0, 0.05, 0.1, 0.15, 0.2) as a cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The effect of Ca doping amount on the structure was examined by scanning electron microscopy (SEM), X-ray diffraction (XRD), thermal expansion, and X-ray photoelectron spectroscopy (XPS).
Titulo: Evaluation of Nd0.8-xSr0.2CaxCoO3-δ(x=0, 0.05, 0.1, 0.15, 0.2) as a cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Electrochemical properties were evaluated for possible application in solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) cathodes.
Titulo: Evaluation of Nd0.8-xSr0.2CaxCoO3-δ(x=0, 0.05, 0.1, 0.15, 0.2) as a cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Results showed that second phase NdCaCoO4+delta is generated when the Ca doping amount is higher than 0.1.
Titulo: Evaluation of Nd0.8-xSr0.2CaxCoO3-δ(x=0, 0.05, 0.1, 0.15, 0.2) as a cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The increase in Ca limits the electronic compensation capacity of the material, resulting in a decrease in thermal expansion coefficient (TEC).
Titulo: Evaluation of Nd0.8-xSr0.2CaxCoO3-δ(x=0, 0.05, 0.1, 0.15, 0.2) as a cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: With the increase of Ca content, the conductivity increases at first and then decreases, and the highest value of 443 S cm(-1) is at x = 0.1 and T = 800 degrees C. Nd0.7Sr0.2Ca0.1CoO3-delta exhibits the lowest area specific resistance of 0.0976 omega cm(2) at 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Evaluation of Nd0.8-xSr0.2CaxCoO3-δ(x=0, 0.05, 0.1, 0.15, 0.2) as a cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The maximum power density of Nd0.7Sr0.2Ca0.1CoO3-delta at 800 degrees C is 409.31 mW cm(-2).
Titulo: Evaluation of Nd0.8-xSr0.2CaxCoO3-δ(x=0, 0.05, 0.1, 0.15, 0.2) as a cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The Ca-doped material maintains good electrochemical properties under the coefficient of thermal expansion (CTE) reduction and thus can be used as an intermediate-temperature SOFC (IT-SOFC) cathode.
Titulo: Evaluation of Nd0.8-xSr0.2CaxCoO3-δ(x=0, 0.05, 0.1, 0.15, 0.2) as a cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
